)"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Revisit "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_highlight_teacher_inst_Italic","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"curious"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Vocabulary Card. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 10–11 "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"The animals on this page all have hair. How many animals with hair are there? Do you see any other features these animals share? "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 12–13 "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"This page is about beaks. Are you curious to learn more about beaks?  "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Why do you think some birds use beaks to clean their feathers? "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(MB)"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 22–23 "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"This book has a glossary in the back, which tells what some words mean. What word are you curious about? "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(MB)"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Extended Play "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Have children explore the classroom to find animals. Challenge children to search the classroom until each child finds three or four animals, and then have everyone return to the circle. Animals can be found in pic